      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i keep getting MLE on this problem. the limits are super tight: 256MB and 1s. i'm using python and even with a basic adjacency list i'm hitting the limit because of how much memory dicts/objects take up. \n\nhere's the problem: \nGiven a graph with N nodes (up to 10^6) and M edges (up to 2*10^5), find the shortest path between node 1 and node N. The edges have weights. \n\nthe judge is being really annoying about memory usage. can u give me a version of Dijkstra that will definitely pass the 256MB limit? i don't care how weird the implementation is, i just need it to not trigger the MLE. i need that AC status.",
